a little note from me to you 🫶🏼 just sitting here on my patio on  a gorgeous day letting my melasma hang out (and prob get worse in the sun lol) and feeling so comfortable in my skin and in myself. I realized not too long ago that I finally feel like I’ve left my “entrepreneurial survival” mode and have finally entered my “thriving” mode. I turn 30 next month and looking back I can’t believe I spent more than half of my 20s self-employed. a year ago today I said yes 😭 park planned the most thoughtful weekend in carmel & big sur before we headed up to sf & santa rosa for the holidays with family and I’ll cherish those memories forever. I remember being soooo happy and I don’t think I’ve ever cried as much 😂 he proposed on a Sunday afternoon, and besides telling our family and close friends, we waited to tell everyone else until late Monday (we took the day off). I’m so glad we did because it felt like our little secret and we just drove up and down hwy 1 and disconnected. it allowed me to be more present!! then of course when I posted, Park broke the internet with our engagement story and went viral with 1.5M views and counting 😂 i love you & adore you & can’t wait to marry you!!!!!!!
